five_yr = data_indicator[['Series Name', 'Country Name', 'Country Code',
                          '2015 [YR2015]','2016 [YR2016]','2017 [YR2017]','2018 [YR2018]', '2019 [YR2019]']]
five_yr = five_yr.dropna() #去掉空value

five_yr = five_yr[~five_yr['2016 [YR2016]'].str.startswith('..')] #去掉没有数据的row
five_yr = five_yr[~five_yr['2015 [YR2015]'].str.startswith('..')]
five_yr = five_yr[~five_yr['2017 [YR2017]'].str.startswith('..')]
five_yr = five_yr[~five_yr['2018 [YR2018]'].str.startswith('..')]
five_yr = five_yr[~five_yr['2019 [YR2019]'].str.startswith('..')]
# five_yr.head()
five_yr = five_yr.apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='ignore')
five_yr['mean'] = five_yr.iloc[:, 3:].mean(axis=1)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.io.shapereader as shpreader
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import cartopy.feature as cfeature

def area(ax, iso, clr) :
    shp = shpreader.natural_earth(resolution='10m',category='cultural',
                                  name='admin_0_countries')
    reader = shpreader.Reader(shp)
    for n in reader.records() :
        if n.attributes['ADM0_A3'] == iso: 
            ax.add_geometries([n.geometry], ccrs.PlateCarree(), facecolor=clr, 
                              alpha = 1.00, linewidth =0.15, edgecolor = "black",
                              label=n.attributes['ADM0_A3']) 
    return ax
iso3 = rst['ios3']
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.Miller())
ax.set_extent([-150, 60, -25, 60])
ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE)
ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS)
ax.add_feature(cfeature.OCEAN)



for n in iso3 :
    area(ax, n, "royalblue")

plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (50,50)
plt.show()

2. international_airline_activity Anaysis¶

Data Description

PaxIn: Revenue passengers inbound to Australian city
FreightInv: Revenue freight in tonnes inbound to Australian city
MailIn: Revenue mail in tonnes inbound to Australian city
PaxOut: Revenue passengers outbound from Australian city
FreightOut: Revenue freight in tonnes outbound from Australian city
MailOut: Revenue mail in tonnes outbound from Australian city
TotalPax: Total revenue passengers inbound and outbound from Australian city
TotalFreight: Total revenue freight in tonnes inbound and outbound from Australian city
TotalMail: Total revenue mail in tonnes inbound and outbound from Australian city
